title: For Sale:  Ares Armor Effin A' Mark 1 Compensator .223/5.56
postcontent:
Will ship this item
The EFFIN-A Compensator was designed to allow the end user the ability to adjust the manner in which the gas exits from the weapon. The EFFIN-A features 7 columns and 4 rows of exit ports that can be either opened or closed through the very simple use of set screws. The exit ports are not threaded completely through to eliminate the possibility of the screw being over turned into the chamber. This feature also allows the screw to "bottom out" increasing tightness and ensuring that it will not work itself out under the pressure of the gasses being released by the weapon. This Compensator also features the ability to "Stack" multiple comps end to end giving further options to the end user.

 Effin-A Compensator MKII is designed to allow users the ability to adjust the manner in which the gas exits from the weapon. The Effin-A Compensator MKII features 8 columns and 3 rows of exit ports that can be either opened or closed through the very simple use of set screws.

Medical issues force sale of this bullpup. Overall length is 26 and 1/4". Barrel length is 16" It's the most sought after rare "sino-soviet" model. Milled receiver; not a cheap yugo or what-have-you.  Chrome-lined barrel with good crown. Was imported as a Cowboy's companion, but the wood stock was pitched when I installed the Bullpup kit.  

It has had a trigger job and most of the trigger creep was removed. It now has positive sear engagement with an estimated 8 lb. trigger pull. It has medium trigger/sear springs yet, so no light strike issues. It was bought in 1993 before the Clinton ban, and I can confirm it has a low round count.

The crown is good and with the 1MOA Eotech, will give ~2MOA from a bench without a bench vise using Import steel ammo. Think Kalishnikov reliability but with better accuracy. It has backup flip-up Magpul sights.

The bolt has been modified to accept magazines with the bolt forward and the bolt does lock back on the last round, so if you're into the tactical/speed thing, that's a plus. You can change mags about as fast as an AK47..

The Eotech is model 511 F revision (fixed battery issue) and the glass has no scratches. Very minor marks on the protective steel hood. It's smaller than the 512 and weighs less. It is NV capable.

There are 5 20-rd Tapco mags with bolt hold-open followers and 1 40-rd steel mag that works fine.  400 rounds of Hollow point Wolf come with it.

I will sell the Eotech separately for $350 firm, but would prefer to sell as a package deal. Asking $1200 for all of it, including the ammunition.
